column5: just took some pics off my iphone on to the puter,i got some nice pics of the spring thaw water release at the buckhorn dam,about half hour from my house,the day i was there i seen the dam automatically open 2 gates and started to take some pictures it was awesome !!! they sure let the water go and it was like that for about 2 weeks,i also have some pics of the bobcaygeon dam a few mins away from where i live also some pics of burliegh falls,the same day...it was amazing to see the water go up 4 ft in a matter of minutes....jpg[/img]fishing/188.jpg[/img]
omg walleye came to my mind
Some great pictures there Shaun, the power of water is always impressive !!

Im with the others cat eye
I always feel my insides churn a little when I'm near a big dam, and I'm a pretty tolerant person.  Sweet pictures.
